cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC 

The paper deals with joint source-channel coding for transmission of correlated sources over multiple access relay channels. This involves techniques from information theory (IT) for optimizing the transmission scheme, multimedia (MM) for dealing with correlated sources, networking and internet architecture (NI) for multiple access relay channels, signal processing (SI) for encoding and decoding, and computational complexity (CC) for analyzing the performance of the proposed scheme. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.CC.
